                        {
                            "key": "XT-21259",
                            "title": "Pricing engine for sales documents",
                            "highlight": false,
                            "content_parts": [
                                {
                                    "content": "<a href=\"https://jira.sage.com/browse/XT-21259\" target=\"_blank\">XT-21259</a>",
                                    "taxonomies": "all"
                                },
                                {
                                    "content": "<p>The following triggers and notification are available for the pricing engine on sales documents:</p><ul><li>If the quantity of a line is changed, the pricing engine is triggered to recalculate the price based on the updated quantity and the existing price lists. The user is asked if they want to accept the recalculation or clear the values.</li><li>When the order date or invoice date on a sales document header is updated the user is asked if they want to update the price and any discount or charge for all the applicable lines according to the defined price lists.</li><li>When the stock site, sales site, sales quantity or sales unit is updated on a sales order line or sales invoice line the user is asked if they want to update the price and any discount or charge according to the defined price lists.</li><li>When the details entered on a document line do not return a price from a defined price list or the price is updated manually, a price list button allows the user to view all the existing defined price lists for the item.</li></ul>",
                                    "taxonomies": "all"
                                }
                            ],
                            "taxonomies": {
                                "software": [
                                    "multi-tenant"
                                ],
                                "version": [
                                    "18.0.0"
                                ]
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "key": "XT-19223",
                            "title": "Sending of purchase orders",
                            "highlight": false,
                            "content_parts": [
                                {
                                    "content": "<a href=\"https://jira.sage.com/browse/XT-19223\" target=\"_blank\">XT-19223</a>",
                                    "taxonomies": "all"
                                },
                                {
                                    "content": "<p>You can send purchase orders as a PDF  to an email recipient. From the <b>Purchase order</b> function, select <b>Send</b> from the <b>More actions</b> icon. The recipient email address defaults from the primary contact details linked to the supplier address that displays on the purchase order. You can select a different supplier contact or you can enter the contact and email address.<br/>When the purchase order is sent to the recipient, the <b>Sending</b> status changes from <b>Not sent</b> to <b>Sent</b>.</p>",
                                    "taxonomies": "all"
                                }
                            ],
                            "taxonomies": {
                                "software": [
                                    "multi-tenant"
                                ],
                                "version": [
                                    "18.0.0"
                                ]
                            }
                        },
                        {
